-- PRESS DIGEST - Hong Kong - Dec 24
-- By Donny Kwok
-- Tue Dec 23, 2014 08:56PM EST
-- None



HONG KONG, Dec 24 (Reuters) - These are some of the leading stories in Hong Kong newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST  -- The Independent Commission Against Corruption has updated its code of conduct for members of public bodies to include tighter restrictions on employees receiving even gifts worth less than HK$500 ($64) without senior approval. It described the update of the guidelines from its 2000 version as a precaution. (http://bit.ly/1AZ1Guy)THE STANDARD -- The High Court has ordered that Deloitte China southern region managing partner Derek Lai Ka-yan and Deloitte China restructuring services principal Darach Haughey be appointed as joint managers of troubled Hong Kong broadcaster ATV. (http://bit.ly/1xeSvbS) -- MTR Corporation <0066.HK> began taking bids for the sixth phase of Lohas Park in Tseung Kwan O, possibly charging a land premium over 17 percent higher than the previous phase, according to market sources. (http://bit.ly/1vlDK0K)MING PAO DAILY -- Cases of fraud using social apps tripled in the first 10 months of the year as compared to the same period last year to a total of 826 cases, involving HK$57 million ($7.4 million), Police Technology Crime Division revealed.